ABUJA – The National Assembly has forwarded the harmonised version of the Nigerian Peace Corps Bill to President Muhammadu Buhari for assent. The transmission of the legislation followed its concurrence by both the Senate and the House of Representatives. Daily Independent gathered that the Clerk to the National Assembly, Sani Tambuwal, by a Correspondence on his official letterhead, dated 12th April, 2023, and addressed to President Buhari, transmitted the bill for assent on Wednesday. Accordingly, three copies of the authenticated bills, INDEPENDENT was told, were sent to the President for the necessary action. Of the three copies, President Buhari would after assenting to the legislation retain one and send back the other assented two copies to the National Assembly for further action. President Buhari has by virtue of the provisions of the 1999 constitution, a 30 days grace, until May 11, 2023, from the day of receipt of the Bills, to assent to it. The existing Peace Corps of Nigeria has been existing on volunteerism, as such, the Bill if assented to, would transform it to a Federal Government owned and funded Agency in the name of Nigeria Peace Corps.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒